echo Welcome to MicroGUI!
echo
echo This desktop works a little bit different than for example the Windows Desktop.
echo The most important thing to get started is that you understand how focus works.
echo
echo You can tell if a window has focus by looking at it's border color. If the border color is cyan then the window is focused.
echo To focus a window either press on the title bar or on the icon in the task bar.
echo
echo To launch programs using the icons on the desktop, the desktop needs to be focused.
echo To focus the desktop you need to press on the left icon in the task bar.
echo You can tell if the desktop is focused or not by looking at the color of the task bar.
echo If the task bar color is cyan then the desktop is focused and the icons can be used.
echo Just use the mouse to click the icon you want to launch.
echo